abstract: The House approved two spending packages on Tuesday, allocating $1.4 trillion and carrying dozens of priorities such as raising the tobacco purchase age nationally to 21.
snippet: The House approved two spending packages on Tuesday, allocating $1.4 trillion and carrying dozens of priorities such as raising the tobacco purchase age nationally to 21.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” The House took the first step on Tuesday to avert a government shutdown, giving overwhelming approval to legislation that would fund all federal agencies and programs through next fall just days before federal funding is set to lapse.
